# Team SDD memory

Before work: read root README, your component README, and `openspec/specs/<domain>/spec.md`. Product shapes live in `spec.md`.

## Hard rules
- No cross-edit: only your folder/branch; talk contracts, never neighbors' files.
- Contract discipline: additive-only mid-sprint; consumers ignore unknown fields.
- Only `orchestration/` imports other components.
- TDD: write or update failing tests before implementation for behavior changes.
- SDD review: OpenSpec + README stay SoT; finish with a review pass.
- Subagents: Grok 4.5 for task implementation and review.

## Git (always branch, PR-only main)
- Always start work from latest `main` on a new feature branch (`git checkout -b feature/<area>`). Never develop on `main`/`master`.
- Never push, force-push, commit, or merge locally into `main`/`master`. Landing is PR-only via the PM/QA merge-gate loop.
- Do not delete remote branches unless the owner explicitly asks.
- Granular commits: one concern per commit (e.g. stub, then tests, then impl, then docs). No mega-commits dumping a whole component.
- After each logical slice (tests green): auto-commit with a concise why-focused message, then `git push -u origin HEAD`.
- Stage only owned/relevant files; never commit secrets (`.env`, keys, tokens). No `--no-verify` unless owner asks.
- Merge conflicts: rebase onto latest `main`; resolve only owned files; keep contracts additive-only; re-test; commit; push. Never edit a teammate's folder to "win."

## Evolution protocol
Update this rule only after reviewed work lands. Add a Learned bullet only for a durable, verified, team-wide convention. Cite source+date; replace stale; no secrets/guesses; max 10 learned bullets; the edit MUST appear in the task diff.

